data.title: Fazende: Five takes on Saints practice #12
data.meta_description: Sean Fazende gives his five takes on Saints practice #12.
data.text:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) - Take One: Windy, physical practice #12

Another day for the Saints, another full-padded workout. That’s now seven so far in the practices they’ve had here in Irvine.

On Wednesday, the wind was the strongest it had been all camp. Plus, the team added in crowd noise to a few of the team periods for the first time. They also had another red zone session.

Dennis Allen said afterward that the team started sluggish but finished stronger.

Take Two: Carr connects with Cedrick Wilson

There are some signs that Derek Carr is getting more comfortable with Cedrick Wilson. On Wednesday, they connected three times. Their first came on a deep over off a play action to Alvin Kamara. Carr fired a strike to Wilson for a big gain.

During the second team period, Carr found Wilson down the sideline on a 9-route for another big gain. Wilson did a nice job of getting his feet down. In the red zone period, Carr found Wilson again on a curl inside the five.

Wilson’s emergence is an important development in the wide receiver room. There are questions about who can be the guy behind Chris Olave and Rashid Shaheed. Wilson is a savvy veteran who is not afraid to block. Right now, I’d put him in the lead for WR3.

Take Three: Top Plays

1vs 1

Kool-Aid McKinstry got his first interception of camp when he wrestled the ball away from Stanley Morgan, Jr. in the back of the end zone.

Many receivers have been running this short out & up type fade route during this period. Wilson and Sampson Nacua both caught touchdowns running this route. Nacua went high to bring down his catch from Carr.

The defense closed out the period on top with a PBU in the end zone. The offense had to do pushups.

7vs7

A.T. Perry caught two dig routes during this period from Jake Haener and Spencer Rattler.

Team #1

Jack Heflin batted a Haener’s pass at the line of scrimmage.

James Robinson had a nice run up the middle for a solid gain.

Team #2

Cam Jordan got in the backfield quickly to shut down Kamara for a loss.

D’Marco Jackson stuffed Jamaal Williams for a loss on a run.

Chase Young beat Oli Udoh on a pressure to force Carr to step up in the pocket. Payton Turner was there for the sack.

Heaner found Perry on a corner route for a 20 yard gain.

Mike Ross sacked Rattler on a bootleg.

Team #3 (red zone)

Young had another pressure on Carr that may have caused a sack.

Taysom Hill scored a touchdown on a fullback dive.

Haener found Perry in the end zone for a score. Perry ran a nice route.

Rattler closed out the period with a touchdown throw to Dallin Holker on an out route.

Developmental Period

Michael Jacobsen made one of the catches of camp on a throw from Rattler. The pair connected again on a bootleg.

Take Four: Attendance Report

Haener was back at work after his skin cancer procedure. Mason Tipton left practice with a hamstring injury.

Paulson Adebo, Demario Davis, Pete Werner, Marshon Lattimore, Rashid Shaheed, Nick Saldiveri, Kendre Miller, Equaminious St. Brown and Jaylan Ford all missed practice.

Juwan Johnson remains on PUP.

Take Five: Other Observations

Lot of buzz about safety Justin Simmons visiting the Saints. If they can work out a contract that benefits both sides, the Saints should absolutely do it. The safety rotation opposite of Tyrann Mathieu has been pretty fluid, but no one has really emerged as that guy. Allen said as much after practice.

This defensive end group is finally living up to their billing in camp. Hopefully, it translates when it counts.

One more practice Thursday before the Saints have their first preseason game Saturday. It’s been a very physical camp ,and this team is ready to hit someone else.
